text: Honestly it looks like a lot of dumb fun which is what i considered the last two, but it also feels like Vin Diesel must be putting his input into the films he works on because all the movies he's in are starting to bleed together stylistically and i'm starting to feel a strange sense of deja vu every time one of his films come to my attention.   What with the same worn out tropes/cliches and cringe inducing dialog where everyone is an untouchable badass until the end of the movie, supporting no actual emotional weight, coupled with CGI distractions and orchestral flourishes to trick us into thinking what watched had some heart to it.  I'm going to see it, but I have the strangest feeling that the best stuff was in the trailer and even if that isn't the case, I'm fearful that most of it will be incredible stock and standard action movie tropes that dummies will devour with smiles.
